<subSubSection id="AE5521D2962F6CA746D9CA9354A84871" pageId="12" pageNumber="57" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="3A9D8B1389FF9728DE819B92D5A236BC" pageId="12" pageNumber="57">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F5AC47FB8D3F009A9B2AA1F5AE92C8A4" pageId="12" pageNumber="57">
There are two Chinese subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="0C56C4BDD78CD6D54B0814D38072AB22" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Biston" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Biston robustum" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustum">Biston robustum</taxonomicName>
, they are 
<taxonomicName id="C1B06AAEDAAA74796EBF04E6864E24F6" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Biston" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Biston robustum subsp. robustum" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="robustum" subSpecies="robustum">Biston robustum robustum</taxonomicName>
Butler, 1879 and 
<taxonomicName id="A01073AAC7C676A0F23B6C5605FC855E" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Biston" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Biston robustum subsp. subrobustum" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="robustum" subSpecies="subrobustum">Biston robustum subrobustum</taxonomicName>
Inoue, 1964 (
<taxonomicName id="1AF4998A20E7DBDD00F0091B9F88F2A4" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Biston" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Biston robustum subsp. subrobustum" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="robustum" subSpecies="subrobustum">Biston robustum subrobustum</taxonomicName>
Inoue, 1964, 
<normalizedToken id="528731C84027927AA0CAF2BEB9108FBA" originalValue="KontyÃ»">Kontyu</normalizedToken>
, 32 (2): 338, pl. 8, fig. 3. Holotype â™‚, Taiwan (central): Puli. (BMNH)). The former is distributed in the mainland China, the latter is distributed in Taiwan. The description of 
<taxonomicName id="C6E4CEADCB922994BA9DCEED9055357F" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Biston" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Biston robustum subsp. kiangsua" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="robustum" subSpecies="kiangsua">Biston robustum kiangsua</taxonomicName>
Wehrli was based on a single, rather aberrant specimen, with a single printed label &quot;Shanghai China&quot;. Similar forms occur in Japan, as mentioned by Wehrli (1941). So this name very probably does not denote a valid subspecies and it is synonymized correctly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
